# cargo-about local-run stderr capture (workspace crates have no license
# field by design — cargo-about warns about them; the warnings are
# expected and benign per about.toml's header comment). The .err file is
# a local debug artifact, not a build output.
cargo-about.err

# Downloaded YARA-Forge release pack — scratch directory used by
# scripts/process-yara-forge-pack.py and the bundle-attributions
# workflow. The unzipped pack is ~7 MB; never committed.
_yara_forge_core/

# Tauri Updater signing keys (TASK-044). Generated locally by
# `cargo run --manifest-path scripts/gen-signing-key/Cargo.toml`; the
# private half lives ONLY in GitHub Actions secrets.
/private/
*.key
*.key.pub

# Session-local Claude Code state (do not commit)
.claude/

# IP scrub (2026-05-11) — pulled out of git history via filter-branch.
# Reference these locally only; never re-add to the public repo.
docs/prd.md
docs/product-vision.md
SECURITY.md

# abuse.ch / MalwareBazaar maintainer-only tooling and its byproducts.
# The feed-builder lives outside the public repo by design:
# - abuse.ch's free non-commercial Auth-Key terms apply per-maintainer,
#   not to the project
# - downloaded sample bytes are never persisted, but the local SQLite
#   cache + the CSV dump + the derived artifacts are maintainer-private
# The mythkernel side consumes the published `crc32_blacklist.bin` +
# `blake3_blacklist.bin` + `blake3_meta.jsonl` artifacts generically —
# any tool that produces them in the documented format works.
tools/feed-builder/
*.csv.zip
*.csv
feed-builder.sqlite*
abusech_*
**/blake3_blacklist.bin
**/crc32_blacklist.bin
**/blake3_meta.jsonl

# Maintainer-local consolidated hash database. The published artifact
# is built FROM this on the maintainer's rig; the multi-GB source DB
# itself is never committed (it'd blow GitHub's 100 MB file ceiling
# and is rebuildable from the feed-builder pipeline anyway).
hash_database/
*.sqlite
*.sqlite-wal
*.sqlite-shm

# TASK-172 NSRL whitelist source + derived. The 169 GB extracted
# RDSv3 SQLite + the much smaller derived `nsrl.sqlite` are both
# maintainer-local; end users download the sorted .bin slices from
# GitHub Releases per TASK-174.
nsrl/
nsrl.sqlite*
**/nsrl_md5.bin
**/nsrl_sha1.bin
**/nsrl_sha256.bin
# Per-OS slices from Wave 2 TASK-183.
**/nsrl_md5_*.bin
**/nsrl_sha1_*.bin
**/nsrl_sha256_*.bin

# TASK-168 tier-aware silver + unified hash bins. Same posture as
# blake3_blacklist.bin above — built locally, shipped via Releases.
**/silver_md5.bin
**/silver_sha256.bin
**/myth_md5.bin
**/myth_sha256.bin
**/myth-blacklist*.sqlite
**/myth-whitelist*.sqlite
